anv: fix assert/crash in import of compressed local memory on xe2+

Backport of Mesa commit 351c5d889cb3 (Lionel Landwerlin, 2026-06-09) onto
media-libs/mesa-26.0.7. Carry locally until the fix lands in a Portage
release. Closes the anv NULL deref that crashes gnome-remote-desktop on
Intel Arc B580 (Xe2) when libva-intel-media-driver (iHD) is present:
importing a compressed local-memory dma-buf without a
VkMemoryDedicatedAllocateInfo leaves image == NULL in the else branch,
then image->vk.format is dereferenced (fault at 0x48).

There is no requirement that imported compressed memory is tied to an
image.

In practice it's unlikely to happen since unless drirc
anv_enable_buffer_comp is enabled we don't list the compressed memory
typed for anything but images. But you can build a case hitting the
assert without even creating an image.

Fixes: 5a05a39e56 ("anv: Limit the SCANOUT flag to color images")
Fixes: b7f7f1c74f ("anv: Treat imported compressed buffers as displayable (xe2)")
Closes: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa/-/work_items/15578
Part-of: <https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa/-/merge_requests/42121>

diff --git a/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c b/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
index bcf9183..e148ed2 100644
--- a/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
+++ b/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
@@ -1622,7 +1622,7 @@ VkResult anv_AllocateMemory(
                VK_EXTERNAL_MEMORY_HANDLE_TYPE_OPAQUE_FD_BIT ||
              fd_info->handleType ==
                VK_EXTERNAL_MEMORY_HANDLE_TYPE_DMA_BUF_BIT_EXT);
-      if (alloc_flags & ANV_BO_ALLOC_COMPRESSED) {
+      if ((alloc_flags & ANV_BO_ALLOC_COMPRESSED) && image != NULL) {
          /* First, when importing a compressed buffer on Xe2+, we are sure
           * about that the buffer is from a resource created with modifiers
           * supporting compression, even the info of modifier is not available
@@ -1640,7 +1640,6 @@ VkResult anv_AllocateMemory(
           * heap and then PAT entry in the later vm_bind stage.
           */
          assert(device->info->ver >= 20);
-         assert(image);
          if (vk_format_is_color(image->vk.format))
             alloc_flags |= ANV_BO_ALLOC_SCANOUT;
       }
